	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=165011><span id=Scholar>Xamurai</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>19 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>and fluxus, I'm not PLing at all I know enough about game to know how much it suffers.&nbsp;&nbsp;I want to be the best rogue I can be, I just figure I'm saving a bit of time on not worrying about as many quests early on, and it gives me more time to still work on my necro and monk progressively as well.  Lately I only work on him when I'm not busy on raiding parties with guild.  My monk and necro are usually on call and I just hit 58 with my necro surprisingly I'm already close to 59 (EMISARRY OF THULE MWAHA!) my necro is on call most of the time if the guild isn't in need of tanks, a necro is quite a powerful group asset if used correctly and I want my rogue to be the same. I know more than my share of the game (not saying I'm a rogue expert, but no lectures cause I've played long enough to know pro's and con's) I know the basics and hey like every other rogue with time and patience I'll learn to play my rogue the way he should be played.  Think about it everyone LEARNS how to play their characters progressively, its how we all started.  For example I remember with my monk at about lvl 20 when fighting during bad pulls etc. I'd let the group bail and I'd take the aggro then I'd mend if I got low and I'd FD letting the mobs go back on their merry little way (until we got revenge and killed the bastards) so if you think about it, even though I might progress easier and maybe faster (not necessarily) I can still learn my role as a rogue just as easy as anyone else.  just another thought I'd like to share with you all... hope it'll give you a little more insight about the type of person I am so you all don't think I'm the guy who spends 24/7 on EQ and has all the best stuff in the game (cause by far I don't)</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
